{"iteration":8,"action":{"reasoning":"Observation: Iteration 7 achieved 79.63% average accuracy using a frozen ViT-B/16 backbone with a replay buffer storing all features and training only a linear head sequentially. The training curves show train_acc ~99% but val_acc ~81%, indicating the persistent linear head is overfitting/memorizing and not finding the best joint solution. Analysis: Because the head is fine-tuned incrementally across tasks, it likely settles into a suboptimal minimum. Since we keep ALL past features in the buffer, we can afford to reinitialize the head before training on each task and optimize from scratch on all observed data — this is essentially the joint-training upper bound. Additionally, switching to a cosine classifier (L2-normalized features + no bias) is known to improve continual learning and generalization. Decision: Update model.py to use a cosine linear head (bias=False, L2 normalize features). Rewrite train.py to (1) reinitialize the head and optimizer at the start of every task, (2) train jointly on the full feature buffer, (3) use AdamW with cosine annealing, (4) add label smoothing and light feature-space Gaussian noise for regularization. Run 20 epochs per task (training is very fast since only a linear head is trained on cached features). Then test predict.py locally and submit eval.","command":"python train.py --epochs 20 --lr 0.01 --label_smoothing 0.1 --feat_noise 0.01","done":false,"files_written":["model.py","predict.py","train.py"]},"command_output":{"exit_code":0,"timed_out":false,"elapsed_seconds":457.31505250930786,"stdout":"","stderr":"2026-04-26 08:08:45,692 - INFO - Device: cuda\n2026-04-26 08:08:50,503 - INFO - Loading pretrained weights from Hugging Face hub (timm/vit_base_patch16_224.augreg_in21k_ft_in1k)\n2026-04-26 08:08:50,614 - INFO - [timm/vit_base_patch16_224.augreg_in21k_ft_in1k] Safe alternative available for 'pytorch_model.bin' (as 'model.safetensors'). Loading weights using safetensors.\n2026-04-26 08: